snippet: Powered by serves that reached 143 miles per hour, second-seeded Milos Raonic of Canada reached his first final of the season by beating Donald Young of the United States, 6-4, 7-5, at the Citi Open in Washington.
lead_paragraph: Powered by serves that reached 143 miles per hour, second-seeded Milos Raonic of Canada reached his first final of the season by beating Donald Young of the United States, 6-4, 7-5, at the Citi Open in Washington.

headline.main: Raonic Advances to Final at Citi Open
